{"title": "Trick Dialogue", "content": "A subversion of the most fundamental aspect of Dialogue: whether a character is talking to someone else or not.\n\nCommonly, a character will appear to be making a brave confession, and then be revealed to have just been practicing before a mirror. Or, he will seem to be explaining his life to someone, and then be shown to be talking to a gravestone.\n\nAlternatively, a character will clearly be talking to himself, but we find out that someone just happened to overhear. (Bonus points if it was the intended recipient of a difficult request.) This can follow on the first kind for a Double Subversion of dialogue.\n\nVisual media typically use a Reveal Shot, often a Close-Up on Head, to execute Trick Dialogue. Compare Fourth Wall Psych (where the character appears to be speaking to the audience but is actually talking to another person). See also Not So Dire.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrickDialogue", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Adventurers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/RanmaOneHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/UsagiYojimbo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/DorkTower", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Firefly", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Scion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/ArchieComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Cinderella", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/OliverAndCompany", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CoolRunnings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Batman1989", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Stardust", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheSixthSense", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ShaunOfTheDead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HotFuzz", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheWorldsEnd", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ReservationRoad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Fargo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AubreyMaturin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/House", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/